entries.femaleVariant: Now let's check Bobby's little find.
I've got green across the board. Good sign.
Where we headed?
All right, fire 'er up.
Punch it, V.
All right, that's probably good.
We still have the nitro to try.
Yeah, I'm game.
I'm game.
There's a flat area over there. Let's swing towards it.
Let's head back.
I'll have to check before tomorrow if her guts are tight and firm. Something just don't sound right to my ear.
I reckon that should do for today.
All right, the afterburner is ready.
Won't get mad if I scratch her up a bit?
Holy shit!
Bobby said there's a scrapyard east of camp.
Hey. How go things?
Perfect spot for a little target practice.
Does it seem like she's tending to the left?
Fixable, ya think?
Just keep shooting at those rust-buckets, I'll recalibrate the targeting on the go.
Are you kidding me? She's a panzer. Panzers don't get scratched up.
What? Everything OK?
Feels better, doesn't it?
Yup, beautiful.
Seems so.
Blast another just to be sure.
Mitch, not gonna be facing a ragtag band of Raffen or an exposed convoy. If we wanna get out of this op alive, they need to have their shit together.
Nervous about tomorrow?
You nervous about tomorrow?
Eh, why the hell not.
It's not a matter of nerves. Not anymore.
Don't you want one?
They're trying. They might even have started to see eye to eye in their own way.
I guess I was hopin' Panam'd mature.
entries.maleVariant: Well, guess I was hopin' Panam'd mature.

entries.femaleVariant: Truly? Thought Saul'd throw in the towel after all that went down.
I'm no pundit on campfire politics, but to my eye… Saul doesn't have a whole lot of wiggle room.
Could just pass the torch to Panam.
He could. But Saul's no brickbrain. He knows Panam doesn't want to fill his boots.
Mature into whom?
C'mon, pretty much obvious Panam oughta lead the clan. Proved it amply.
The only thing she proved is that she cares. But don't confuse that with wanting power.
Yeah, it's just now I know why nobody puts nitro in these.
[Take beer] Why not.
I'm good, thanks.
I'm good, thanks.
Back during the war, before we were first deployed, we were trained to keep stress in check. Do you want to know how?
They gave us chem-cocktails. Supplements, boosters – God knows what else.
[pl_pl][MITCH wyrzuca / odkłada pustą butelkę.]
All right, we've gossiped enough for one day.
What was just spoken stays between us, OK? I'm 'onna poke around some in this baby's insides.
[pl_pl][MITCH moves to the entrance of the panzer.]
Right. Happy hunting, Mitch.
Hell, by now they both know what's expected of them, what the clan expects of them.
Least tell me Saul offered Panam a seat at the table.
And what gave you the idea Panam wants a seat to begin with?
So she got cold feet.
Think I get it. Panam's about the clan, not power. Question is whether she can reconcile the two.
I thought you knew her better.
Hmm.
Panam has decided to risk her life, our lives, for you and only you. So I don't think I'd dare to call that cold feet.
No, not what I... What I meant was…
Hey, don't look at me.
It's all good, V. I get it.
Hop in.
How?
After a dozen sessions, something clicks in your brain. Neural pathways get rewired – the part of you that generates fear is zapped into oblivion.
So, don't fear a thing, do you?
Fucked up, that.
Thought they banned chem-cocktails because of cyberpsychosis.
Thought they banned chem-cocktails – during the war, even.
Please.
Weren't there outbreaks of cyberpsychosis within units?
And? Do you think Militech gave a lick about that? They just airlifted the afflicted to their clinics in Taiwan, daily flights.
And every day we'd get fresh recruits. Still, they pumped us with that shit. But hey, we couldn't argue with the money.
So, not afraid of anything at this point?
If only it was that simple.
I'm not concerned about tomorrow – raids like that are second nature. It's what's going on in the camp…
Eh, no matter. I'm talking silly now.
That's seriously fucked up.
Whad'ya think? That war wasn't effed up?
One we'll head into tomorrow, too?
Why? Ya havin' second thoughts?
I'm not worried about it. And neither should you be. Something else will be keeping me awake.
What's that?
Eh, no matter.
Come on – gotta tell me.
OK, see you first thing tomorrow.
C'mon. All in the family now, isn't it?
The truth is I'm concerned about the goings on between Panam and Saul.
They seem to think that putting on a brave face for everyone is enough. But folks here aren't slow.
There's gossip spreading like wildfire already – that Saul won't pull through, that he's in it for himself. That this family needs a shake-up.
And? They right?
And your take?
Hope it won't all spill into tomorrow.
And? They right?
They are. But nobody knows comes next.
What about you?
What about me?
What's your take? Saul oughta step down, pass the torch to Panam?
We'll see how things look tomorrow, once the smoke has cleared.
Don't wanna come off as an ungrateful bitch, but really hope this camp morale doesn't spill into tomorrow.
entries.maleVariant: Don't wanna come off as an ungrateful ass, but really hope this camp morale doesn't spill into tomorrow.

entries.femaleVariant: It won't. Saul and Panam did one thing right at least – they welcomed you into the clan. Not a one will abandon you in your hour of need.
It's like this, see – Panam's hell-bent on helping you. But Saul sees this whole thing as an opportunity.
Possible loot from Mikoshi?
Mhm. If we pull this off, get our hands on some sweet Arasaka tech that will set us up down south... Do you follow?
It'll ease folks' worries, buy Saul time.
Panam'll lose her chance at leadership.
It'll ease folks' fears, buy Saul some time.
[pl_pl][kiwa głową, unosi butelkę na znak, że V dobrze kombinuje]
Saul's a smooth operator. He knows what he's doing. Let's just hope he hasn't overplayed his hand.
Panam'll lose her chance at taking the helm.
If she hasn't lost it already. Here's how it looks – tomorrow goes off without a hitch, Saul gets the credit for leading.
But if anything goes sideways…
Blame falls on Panam. She's the one who brought me into the fold.
entries.maleVariant: Blame falls on Panam. She's the one brought me into the fold.

entries.femaleVariant: I get it. Don't wanna talk about it, no pressure.
Let's just make sure everyone does what they're supposed to do tomorrow.
Sounds good.
You get some rest. I'll try tweaking that targeting. See you at sunup.
Take care.
This one's more likely to fall apart after we fire it up.
Thought Saul would cave.
Was hopin' Panam would mature.
Need to settle their differences if this plan's gonna work.
So she got cold feet.
She cares about the clan, not power.
Your turn – what do you reckon?
Sure she's ready?
Is she ready for me?
You know me – I'd gladly spend another two days on 'er, but this will have to do.
Hop in, let's see what's she's made of.
They shot them into our veins. Our biomons went wild, but only for a second before stabilizing. And boy did we stabilize.
So, time for a ride?
You'll be steering this beaut tomorrow. Would you like to give her a whirl?
Still can't get over the surprise.
What just happened – still can't quite wrap my head around it.
Hardly anyone ever does. The day you get your jacket is a day you never forget.
Better than ever. You?
Good. Really good, in fact. How 'bout you?
I'm trying to get the panzer running. She's stubborn, our dame, but I won't give, either.
Are we heading back?
Try hitting the targets with the throttle wide open! Let's see if she's synced up.
I'll take her now. I get picky about parking.
V? Is something up?
Are you drinking and driving or not?
Um, is everything all right?
You'e awfully quiet. Is something up?
Earth to V? Your cogs're grinding – what about?
Get in and let's go.
[Get in]
